result.execSummary:
The defendant Daniel A. Aguilar was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Daniel A. Aguilar is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

records.addlTxt:
10:31 am - Defendant Daniel A. Aguilar appeared in court. Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin. DA states agreement. Court questions defendant regarding right to attorney. Defendant waives right to attorney. Defendant pleads NO CONTEST to Ct. 2.   Court questions DE regarding the plea.  DA explains elements of charge.  Court finds plea/waiver to be free, etc.  Court finds factual basis does exist.  DA certifies victims rights compliance. Court accepts plea, finds DE guilty and orders entry of JOC on Ct. 2 and on motion of DA dismisses Ct. 1.  Comments by parties. Comments and ruling by Court. Appeal rights given. Adj. 10:48 am. 
Court imposes (Ct. 2): Sentence withheld - 9 months probation.
Conditions: $300 fine; $200 DNAAS and submit sample; $72.63 SBDA; Apology; AODA; 10 day jail term, with huber privileges, may be served in any county, to commence within 30 days from 12-09-15; May NOT go upon premises of Harbor View; NO CONTACT with Justin Pisca.

If not already completed DE must submit to booking at Sheriff's Dept prior to release. Defendant shall give written notice prior to any change in address or telephone number to the Clerk of this Court and Defense Attorney.  DE may not have contact with Justin Pisca, unless there is written consent on file nor go upon Harbor View premises.

Defendant Daniel A. Aguilar appeared in court. Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint acknowledged, reading waived.  DE waives right to attorney.  DE enters plea of NOT GUILTY to all counts.  Court orders Pre-trial conference be scheduled.
